The verbose flag of scp does not suppress two lines of logging for every
transmitted file. There is an example below. I think if verbose is set to false,
these logs should also be suppressed.

      [scp] Sending File: LICENSE : 11558
      [scp] File transfer time: 0,06 Average Rate: 183.460,32 B/s


The implementation could be easily achieved by adding :
	@Override
	public void log( String msg ) {
		log(msg, this.getVerbose() ? Project.MSG_DEBUG : Project.MSG_INFO);
	}
